Explanation:

We use a hash map to store the count of each character in the first string. Then, we iterate over the second string and decrement the count of each character in the hash map. Finally, we iterate over the hash map to calculate the sum of the squared counts of the characters in the first string. This solution has a time complexity of O(n) and space complexity of O(n), where n is the length of the strings.

